  19,2,ňĻThis isňļ a reminder of your Lord‚Äôs mercy to His servant Zachariah
  19,3,when he cried out to his Lord privately
  19,4,"saying, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Surely my bones have become brittle, and grey hair has spread across my head, but I have never been disappointed in my prayer to You, my Lord"
  19,5,"And I am concerned about ňĻthe faith ofňļ my relatives after me, since my wife is barren. So grant me, by Your grace, an heir"
  19,6,"who will inherit ňĻprophethoodňļ from me and the family of Jacob, and make him, O Lord, pleasing ňĻto Youňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  19,7,"ňĻThe angels announced,ňļ ‚ÄúO Zachariah! Indeed, We give you the good news of ňĻthe birth ofňļ a son, whose name will be John‚ÄĒa name We have not given to anyone before.‚ÄĚ"
  19,8,"He wondered, ‚ÄúMy Lord! How can I have a son when my wife is barren, and I have become extremely old?‚ÄĚ"
  19,9,"An angel replied, ‚ÄúSo will it be! Your Lord says, ‚ÄėIt is easy for Me, just as I created you before, when you were nothing!‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  19,10,"Zachariah said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Grant me a sign.‚ÄĚ He responded, ‚ÄúYour sign is that you will not ňĻbe able toňļ speak to people for three nights, despite being healthy.‚ÄĚ"
  19,11,"So he came out to his people from the sanctuary, signalling to them to glorify ňĻGodňļ morning and evening"
  19,12,"ňĻIt was later said,ňļ ‚ÄúO John! Hold firmly to the Scriptures.‚ÄĚ And We granted him wisdom while ňĻhe was stillňļ a child"
  19,13,as well as purity and compassion from Us. And he was God-fearing
  19,14,and kind to his parents. He was neither arrogant nor disobedient
  19,15,"Peace be upon him the day he was born, and the day of his death, and the day he will be raised back to life"
  19,16,"And mention in the Book ňĻO Prophet, the story ofňļ Mary when she withdrew from her family to a place in the east"
  19,17,"screening herself off from them. Then We sent to her Our angel, ňĻGabriel,ňļ appearing before her as a man, perfectly formed"
  19,18,"She appealed, ‚ÄúI truly seek refuge in the Most Compassionate from you! ňĻSo leave me aloneňļ if you are God-fearing.‚ÄĚ"
  19,19,"He responded, ‚ÄúI am only a messenger from your Lord, ňĻsentňļ to bless you with a pure son.‚ÄĚ"
  19,20,"She wondered, ‚ÄúHow can I have a son when no man has ever touched me, nor am I unchaste?‚ÄĚ"
  19,21,"He replied, ‚ÄúSo will it be! Your Lord says, ‚ÄėIt is easy for Me. And so will We make him a sign for humanity and a mercy from Us.‚Äô It is a matter ňĻalreadyňļ decreed.‚ÄĚ"
  19,22,So she conceived him and withdrew with him to a remote place
  19,23,"Then the pains of labour drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She cried, ‚ÄúAlas! I wish I had died before this, and was a thing long forgotten!‚ÄĚ"
  19,24,"So a voice¬†reassured her from below her, ‚ÄúDo not grieve! Your Lord has provided a stream at your feet"
  19,25,"And shake the trunk of this palm tree towards you, it will drop fresh, ripe dates upon you"
  19,26,"So eat and drink, and put your heart at ease. But if you see any of the people, say, ‚ÄėI have vowed silence¬†to the Most Compassionate, so I am not talking to anyone today.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  19,27,"Then she returned to her people, carrying him. They said ňĻin shockňļ, ‚ÄúO Mary! You have certainly done a horrible thing"
  19,28,"O sister of Aaron!¬†Your father was not an indecent man, nor was your mother unchaste.‚ÄĚ"
  19,29,"So she pointed to the baby. They exclaimed, ‚ÄúHow can we talk to someone who is an infant in the cradle?‚ÄĚ"
  19,30,"ňĻJesusňļ declared, ‚ÄúI am truly a servant of God. He has destined me to be given the Scripture and to be a prophet"
  19,31,"He has made me a blessing wherever I go, and bid me to establish prayer and give alms-tax as long as I live"
  19,32,and to be kind to my mother. He has not made me arrogant or defiant
  19,33,"Peace be upon me the day I was born, the day I die, and the day I will be raised back to life!‚ÄĚ"
  19,34,"That is Jesus, son of Mary. ňĻAnd this isňļ a word of truth, about which they dispute"
  19,35,"It is not for God to take a son! Glory be to Him. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
  19,36,"ňĻJesus also declared,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely God is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him ňĻaloneňļ. This is the Straight Path.‚ÄĚ"
  19,37,"Yet their ňĻvariousňļ groups have differed among themselves ňĻabout himňļ, so woe to the disbelievers when they face a tremendous Day"
  19,38,How clearly will they hear and see on the Day they will come to Us! But today the wrongdoers are clearly astray
  19,39,"And warn them ňĻO Prophetňļ of the Day of Regret, when all matters will be settled, while they are ňĻengrossedňļ in heedlessness and disbelief"
  19,40,"Indeed, it is We Who will succeed the earth and whoever is on it. And to Us they will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  19,41,"And mention in the Book ňĻO Prophet, the story ofňļ Abraham. He was surely a man of truth and a prophet"
  19,42,"ňĻRememberňļ when he said to his father, ‚ÄúO dear father! Why do you worship what can neither hear nor see, nor benefit you at all"
  19,43,"O dear father! I have certainly received some knowledge which you have not received, so follow me and I will guide you to the Straight Path"
  19,44,O dear father! Do not worship Satan. Surely Satan is ever rebellious against the Most Compassionate
  19,45,"O dear father! I truly fear that you will be touched by a torment from the Most Compassionate, and become Satan‚Äôs companion ňĻin Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  19,46,"He threatened, ‚ÄúHow dare you reject my idols, O Abraham! If you do not desist, I will certainly stone you ňĻto deathňļ. So be gone from me for a long time!‚ÄĚ"
  19,47,"Abraham responded, ‚ÄúPeace be upon you! I will pray to my Lord for your forgiveness. He has truly been Most Gracious to me"
  19,48,"As I distance myself from ňĻall ofňļ you and from whatever you invoke besides God, I will ňĻcontinue toňļ call upon my Lord ňĻaloneňļ, trusting that I will never be disappointed in invoking my Lord.‚ÄĚ"
  19,49,"So after he had left them and what they worshipped besides God, We granted him Isaac and Jacob, and made each of them a prophet"
  19,50,"We showered them with Our mercy, and blessed them with honourable mention"
  19,51,"And mention in the Book ňĻO Prophet, the story ofňļ Moses. He was truly a chosen man, and was a messenger and a prophet"
  19,52,"We called him from the right side of Mount ŠĻ¨√Ľr, and drew him near, speaking ňĻwith himňļ directly"
  19,53,"And We appointed for him‚ÄĒout of Our grace‚ÄĒhis brother, Aaron, as a prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the Book ňĻO Prophet, the story ofňļ Ishmael. He was truly a man of his word, and was a messenger and a prophet"
  19,55,He used to urge his people to pray and give alms-tax. And his Lord was well pleased with him
  19,56,"And mention in the Book ňĻO Prophet, the story ofňļ Enoch. He was surely a man of truth and a prophet"
  19,57,And We elevated him to an honourable status
  19,58,"Those were ňĻsome ofňļ the prophets who God has blessed from among the descendants of Adam, and of those We carried with Noah ňĻin the Arkňļ, and of the descendants of Abraham and Israel,¬†and of those We ňĻrightlyňļ guided and chose. Whenever the revelations of the Most Compassionate were recited to them, they fell down, prostrating and weeping"
  19,59,But they were succeeded by generations who neglected prayer and followed their lusts and so will soon face the evil consequences
  19,60,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good, it is they who will be admitted into Paradise, never being denied any reward"
  19,61,"ňĻThey will be inňļ the Gardens of Eternity, promised in trust by the Most Compassionate to His servants. Surely His promise will be fulfilled"
  19,62,There they will never hear any idle talk‚ÄĒonly ňĻgreetings ofňļ peace. And there they will have their provisions morning and evening
  19,63,"That is Paradise, which We will grant to whoever is devout among Our servants"
  19,64,"‚ÄúWe only descend by the command of your Lord. To Him belongs whatever is before us, and whatever is behind us, and everything in between. And your Lord is never forgetful"
  19,65,"ňĻHe is theňļ Lord of the heavens, and the earth, and everything in between. So worship Him ňĻaloneňļ, and be steadfast in His worship. Do you know of anyone equal to Him ňĻin His attributesňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  19,66,"Yet ňĻsomeňļ people ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúAfter I die, will I really be raised to life again?‚ÄĚ"
  19,67,"Do ňĻsuchňļ people not remember that We created them before, when they were nothing"
  19,68,"By your Lord ňĻO Prophetňļ! We will surely gather them along with the devils, and then set them around Hell on their knees"
  19,69,Then We will certainly begin by dragging out of every group the ones most defiant to the Most Compassionate
  19,70,And We truly know best who is most deserving of burning in it
  19,71,There is none of you who will not pass over it.¬†ňĻThis isňļ a decree your Lord must fulfil
  19,72,"Then We will deliver those who were devout, leaving the wrongdoers there on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers ask the believers ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhich of the two of us is better in status and superior in assembly?‚ÄĚ"
  19,74,"ňĻImagine, O Prophetňļ how many peoples We have destroyed before them, who were far better in luxury and splendour"
  19,75,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhoever is ňĻentrenchedňļ in misguidance, the Most Compassionate will allow them plenty of time, until‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthey face what they are threatened with: either the torment or the Hour. Only then will they realize who is worse in position and inferior in manpower.‚ÄĚ"
  19,76,And God increases in guidance those who are ňĻrightlyňļ guided. And the everlasting good deeds are far better with your Lord in reward and in outcome
  19,77,"Have you seen ňĻO Prophetňļ the one¬†who rejects Our revelations yet boasts, ‚ÄúI will definitely be granted ňĻplenty ofňļ wealth and children ňĻif there is an afterlifeňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  19,78,Has he looked into the unseen or taken a pledge from the Most Compassionate
  19,79,Not at all! We certainly record whatever he claims and will increase his punishment extensively
  19,80,"And We will inherit what he boasts of, and he will come before Us all by himself"
  19,81,"They have taken other gods, instead of God, seeking strength ňĻand protectionňļ through them"
  19,82,But no! Those ňĻgodsňļ will deny their worship and turn against them
  19,83,"Do you ňĻO Prophetňļ not see that We have sent the devils against the disbelievers, constantly inciting them"
  19,84,"So do not be in haste against them, for indeed We are ňĻcloselyňļ counting down their days"
  19,85,ňĻWatch forňļ the Day We will gather the righteous before the Most Compassionate as an honoured delegation
  19,86,and drive the wicked to Hell like a thirsty herd
  19,87,"None will have the right to intercede, except those who have taken a covenant from the Most Compassionate"
  19,88,"They¬†say, ‚ÄúThe Most Compassionate has offspring.‚ÄĚ"
  19,89,You have certainly made an outrageous claim
  19,90,"by which the heavens are about to burst, the earth to split apart, and the mountains to crumble to pieces"
  19,91,in protest of attributing children to the Most Compassionate
  19,92,It does not befit ňĻthe majesty ofňļ the Most Compassionate to have children
  19,93,There is none in the heavens or the earth who will not return to the Most Compassionate in full submission
  19,94,"Indeed, He fully knows them and has counted them precisely"
  19,95,And each of them will return to Him on the Day of Judgment all alone
  19,96,"As for those who believe and do good, the Most Compassionate will ňĻcertainlyňļ bless them with ňĻgenuineňļ love"
  19,97,"Indeed, We have made this ňĻQuranňļ easy in your own language ňĻO Prophetňļ so with it you may give good news to the righteous and warn those who are contentious"
  19,98,"ňĻImagineňļ how many peoples We have destroyed before them! Do you ňĻstillňļ see any of them, or ňĻevenňļ hear from them the slightest sound"
