  20,12,"It is truly I. I am your Lord! So take off your sandals, for you are in the sacred valley of ŠĻ¨uwa"
  20,13,"I have chosen you, so listen to what is revealed"
  20,14,"‚ÄėIt is truly I. I am God! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Me. So worship Me ňĻaloneňļ, and establish prayer for My remembrance"
  20,15,"The Hour is sure to come. My Will is to keep it hidden, so that every soul may be rewarded according to their efforts"
  20,16,"So do not let those who disbelieve in it and follow their desires distract you from it, or you will be doomed.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  20,17,"ňĻGod added,ňļ ‚ÄúAnd what is that in your right hand, O Moses?‚ÄĚ"
  20,18,"He replied, ‚ÄúIt is my staff! I lean on it, and with it I beat down ňĻbranchesňļ for my sheep, and have other uses for it.‚ÄĚ"
  20,19,"God said, ‚ÄúThrow it down, O Moses!‚ÄĚ"
  20,20,"So he did, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒit became a serpent, slithering"
  20,21,"God said, ‚ÄúTake it, and have no fear. We will return it to its former state"
  20,22,"And put your hand under your armpit, it will come out ňĻshiningňļ white, unblemished,¬†as another sign"
  20,23,so that We may show you some of Our greatest signs
  20,24,"Go to Pharaoh, for he has truly transgressed ňĻall boundsňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,25,"Moses prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Uplift my heart for me"
  20,26,and make my task easy
  20,27,and remove the impediment from my tongue
  20,28,so people may understand my speech
  20,29,and grant me a helper from my family
  20,30,"Aaron, my brother"
  20,31,Strengthen me through him
  20,32,and let him share my task
  20,33,so that we may glorify You much
  20,34,and remember You much
  20,35,for truly You have ňĻalwaysňļ been overseeing us.‚ÄĚ
  20,36,"God responded, ‚ÄúAll that you requested has been granted, O Moses"
  20,37,And surely We had shown You favour before
  20,38,when We inspired your mother with this
  20,39,"‚ÄėPut him into a chest, then put it into the river. The river will wash it ashore, and he will be taken by ňĻPharaoh,ňļ an enemy of Mine and his.‚Äô And I blessed you with lovability from Me¬†ňĻO Mosesňļ so that you would be brought up under My ňĻwatchfulňļ Eye"
  20,40,"ňĻRememberňļ when your sister came along and proposed, ‚ÄėShall I direct you to someone who will nurse him?‚Äô¬†So We reunited you with your mother so that her heart would be put at ease, and she would not grieve. ňĻLaterňļ you killed a man ňĻby mistakeňļ, but We saved you from sorrow, as well as other tests We put you through. Then you stayed for a number of years among the people of Midian. Then you came here as pre-destined, O Moses"
  20,41,And I have selected you for My service
  20,42,"Go forth, you and your brother, with My signs and never falter in remembering Me"
  20,43,"Go, both of you, to Pharaoh, for he has truly transgressed ňĻall boundsňļ"
  20,44,"Speak to him gently, so perhaps he may be mindful ňĻof Meňļ or fearful ňĻof My punishmentňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,45,"They both pleaded, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We fear that he may be quick to harm us or act tyrannically.‚ÄĚ"
  20,46,"God reassured ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúHave no fear! I am with you, hearing and seeing"
  20,47,"So go to him and say, ‚ÄėIndeed we are both messengers from your Lord, so let the Children of Israel go with us, and do not oppress them. We have come to you with a sign from your Lord. And salvation will be for whoever follows the ňĻrightňļ guidance"
  20,48,It has indeed been revealed to us that the punishment will be upon whoever denies ňĻthe truthňļ and turns away.‚Äô‚ÄĚ
  20,49,"Pharaoh asked, ‚ÄúWho then is the Lord of you two, O Moses?‚ÄĚ"
  20,50,"He answered, ‚ÄúOur Lord is the One Who has given everything its ňĻdistinctiveňļ form, then guided ňĻitňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,51,"Pharaoh asked, ‚ÄúAnd what about previous peoples?‚ÄĚ"
  20,52,"He replied, ‚ÄúThat knowledge is with my Lord in a Record. My Lord neither falters¬†nor forgets ňĻanythingňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,53,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who has laid out the earth for ňĻall ofňļ you, and set in it pathways for you, and sends down rain from the sky, causing various types of plants to grow"
  20,54,ňĻsoňļ eat and graze your cattle. Surely in this are signs for people of sound judgment
  20,55,"From the earth We created you, and into it We will return you, and from it We will bring you back again"
  20,56,"And We certainly showed Pharaoh all of Our signs,¬†but he denied them and refused ňĻto believeňļ"
  20,57,"He said, ‚ÄúHave you come to drive us out of our land with your magic, O Moses"
  20,58,"We can surely meet you with similar magic. So set for us an appointment that neither of us will fail to keep, in a central place.‚ÄĚ"
  20,59,"Moses said, ‚ÄúYour appointment is on the Day of the Festival, and let the people be gathered mid-morning.‚ÄĚ"
  20,60,"Pharaoh then withdrew, orchestrated his scheme, then returned"
  20,61,"Moses warned the magicians, ‚ÄúWoe to you! Do not fabricate a lie against God,¬†or He will wipe you out with a torment. Whoever fabricates ňĻliesňļ is bound to fail.‚ÄĚ"
  20,62,"So the magicians disputed the matter among themselves, conversing privately"
  20,63,"They concluded, ‚ÄúThese two are only magicians who want to drive you out of your land with their magic, and do away with your most cherished traditions"
  20,64,"So orchestrate your plan, then come forward in ňĻperfectňļ ranks. And whoever prevails today will certainly be successful.‚ÄĚ"
  20,65,"They said, ‚ÄúO Moses! Either you cast, or let us be the first to cast.‚ÄĚ"
  20,66,"Moses responded, ‚ÄúNo, you go first.‚ÄĚ And suddenly their ropes and staffs appeared to him‚ÄĒby their magic‚ÄĒto be slithering"
  20,67,So Moses concealed fear within himself
  20,68,"We reassured ňĻhimňļ, ‚ÄúDo not fear! It is certainly you who will prevail"
  20,69,"Cast what is in your right hand, and it will swallow up what they have made, for what they have made is no more than a magic trick. And magicians can never succeed wherever they go.‚ÄĚ"
  20,70,"So the magicians fell down in prostration, declaring, ‚ÄúWe believe in the Lord of Aaron and Moses.‚ÄĚ"
  20,71,"Pharaoh threatened, ‚ÄúHow dare you believe in him before I give you permission? He must be your master who taught you magic. I will certainly cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, and crucify you on the trunks of palm trees. You will really see whose punishment is more severe and more lasting.‚ÄĚ"
  20,72,"They responded, ‚ÄúBy the One Who created us! We will never prefer you over the clear proofs that have come to us. So do whatever you want! Your authority only covers the ňĻfleetingňļ life of this world"
  20,73,"Indeed, we have believed in our Lord so He may forgive our sins and that magic you have forced us to practice. And God is far superior ňĻin rewardňļ and more lasting ňĻin punishmentňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,74,"Whoever comes to their Lord as an evildoer will certainly have Hell, where they can neither live nor die"
  20,75,"But whoever comes to Him as a believer, having done good, they will have the highest ranks"
  20,76,"the Gardens of Eternity, under which rivers flow, where they will stay forever. That is the reward of those who purify themselves"
  20,77,"And We surely inspired Moses, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúLeave with My servants ňĻat nightňļ and strike a dry passage for them across the sea. Have no fear of being overtaken, nor be concerned ňĻof drowningňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,78,Then Pharaoh pursued them with his soldiers‚ÄĒbut how overwhelming were the waters that submerged them
  20,79,"And ňĻsoňļ Pharaoh led his people astray, and did not guide ňĻthem rightlyňļ"
  20,80,"O Children of Israel! We saved you from your enemy, and made an appointment with you¬†on the right side of Mount ŠĻ¨√Ľr, and sent down to you manna and quails"
  20,81,"ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúEat from the good things We have provided for you, but do not transgress in them, or My wrath will befall you. And whoever My wrath befalls is certainly doomed"
  20,82,"But I am truly Most Forgiving to whoever repents, believes, and does good, then persists on ňĻtrueňļ guidance.‚ÄĚ"
  20,83,"ňĻGod asked,ňļ ‚ÄúWhy have you come with such haste ahead of your people, O Moses?‚ÄĚ"
  20,84,"He replied, ‚ÄúThey are close on my tracks. And I have hastened to You, my Lord, so You will be pleased.‚ÄĚ"
  20,85,"God responded, ‚ÄúWe have indeed tested your people in your absence, and the S√Ęmiri¬†has led them astray.‚ÄĚ"
  20,86,"So Moses returned to his people, furious and sorrowful. He said, ‚ÄúO my people! Had your Lord not made you a good promise?¬†Has my absence been too long for you? Or have you wished for wrath from your Lord to befall you, so you broke your promise to me?‚ÄĚ"
  20,87,"They argued, ‚ÄúWe did not break our promise to you of our own free will, but we were made to carry the burden of the people‚Äôs ňĻgoldenňļ jewellery,¬†then we threw it ňĻinto the fireňļ, and so did the S√Ęmiri.‚ÄĚ"
  20,88,"Then he moulded for them an idol of a calf that made a lowing sound. They said, ‚ÄúThis is your god and the god of Moses, but Moses forgot ňĻwhere it wasňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  20,89,"Did they not see that it did not respond to them, nor could it protect or benefit them"
  20,90,"Aaron had already warned them beforehand, ‚ÄúO my people! You are only being tested by this, for indeed your ňĻone trueňļ Lord is the Most Compassionate. So follow me and obey my orders.‚ÄĚ"
  20,91,"They replied, ‚ÄúWe will not cease to worship it until Moses returns to us.‚ÄĚ"
  20,92,"Moses scolded ňĻhis brotherňļ, ‚ÄúO Aaron! What prevented you, when you saw them going astray"
  20,93,from following after me? How could you disobey my orders?‚ÄĚ
  20,94,"Aaron pleaded, ‚ÄúO son of my mother! Do not seize me by my beard or ňĻthe hair ofňļ my head. I really feared that you would say, ‚ÄėYou have caused division among the Children of Israel, and did not observe my word.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  20,95,"Moses then asked, ‚ÄúWhat did you think you were doing, O S√Ęmiri?‚ÄĚ"
  20,96,"He said, ‚ÄúI saw what they did not see, so I took a handful ňĻof dustňļ from the hoof-prints of ňĻthe horse ofňļ the messenger-angel ňĻGabrielňļ then cast it ňĻon the moulded calfňļ. This is what my lower-self tempted me into.‚ÄĚ"
  20,97,"Moses said, ‚ÄúGo away then! And for ňĻthe rest of yourňļ life you will surely be crying, ‚ÄėDo not touch ňĻmeňļ!‚Äô¬†Then you will certainly have a fate¬†that you cannot escape. Now look at your god to which you have been devoted: we will burn it up, then scatter it in the sea completely.‚ÄĚ"
  20,98,"ňĻThen Moses addressed his people,ňļ ‚ÄúYour only god is God, there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. He encompasses everything in ňĻHisňļ knowledge.‚ÄĚ"
  20,99,This is how We relate to you ňĻO Prophetňļ some of the stories of the past. And We have certainly granted you a Reminder¬†from Us
  20,100,Whoever turns away from it will surely bear the burden ňĻof sinňļ on the Day of Judgment
  20,101,suffering its consequences forever. What an evil burden they will carry on Judgment Day
  20,102,"ňĻBeware ofňļ the Day the Trumpet will be blown,¬†and We will gather the wicked on that Day blue-faced ňĻfrom horror and thirstňļ"
  20,103,"They will whisper among themselves, ‚ÄúYou stayed no more than ten days ňĻon the earthňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  20,104,"We know best what they will say‚ÄĒthe most reasonable of them will say, ‚ÄúYou stayed no more than a day.‚ÄĚ"
  20,105,"And ňĻifňļ they ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about the mountains, ňĻthenňļ say, ‚ÄúMy Lord will wipe them out completely"
  20,106,leaving the earth level and bare
  20,107,with neither depressions nor elevations to be seen.‚ÄĚ
  20,108,"On that Day all will follow the caller ňĻfor assemblyňļ, ňĻandňļ none will dare to deviate. All voices will be hushed before the Most Compassionate. Only whispers¬†will be heard"
  20,109,"On that Day no intercession will be of any benefit, except by those granted permission by the Most Compassionate and whose words are agreeable to Him"
  20,110,"He ňĻfullyňļ knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them,¬†but they cannot encompass Him in ňĻtheirňļ knowledge"
  20,111,"And all faces will be humbled before the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining. And those burdened with wrongdoing will be in loss"
  20,112,But whoever does good and is a believer will have no fear of being wronged or denied ňĻtheir rewardňļ
  20,113,"And so We have sent it down as an Arabic Quran and varied the warnings in it, so perhaps they will shun evil or it may cause them to be mindful"
  20,114,"Exalted is God, the True King! Do not rush to recite ňĻa revelation ofňļ the Quran ňĻO Prophetňļ before it is ňĻproperlyňļ conveyed to you,¬†and pray, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Increase me in knowledge.‚ÄĚ"
  20,115,"And indeed, We once made a covenant with Adam, but he forgot, and ňĻsoňļ We did not find determination in him"
  20,116,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We said to the angels, ‚ÄúProstrate before Adam,‚ÄĚ so they all did‚ÄĒbut not Ibl√ģs,¬†who refused ňĻarrogantlyňļ"
  20,117,"So We cautioned, ‚ÄúO Adam! This is surely an enemy to you and to your wife. So do not let him drive you both out of Paradise, for you ňĻO Adamňļ would then suffer ňĻhardshipňļ"
  20,118,Here it is guaranteed that you will never go hungry or unclothed
  20,119,nor will you ňĻeverňļ suffer from thirst or ňĻthe sun‚Äôsňļ heat.‚ÄĚ
  20,120,"But Satan whispered to him, saying, ‚ÄúO Adam! Shall I show you the Tree of Immortality and a kingdom that does not fade away?‚ÄĚ"
  20,121,"So they both ate from the tree and then their nakedness was exposed to them, prompting them to cover themselves with leaves from Paradise. So Adam disobeyed his Lord, and ňĻsoňļ lost his way"
  20,122,"Then his Lord chose him ňĻfor His graceňļ, accepted his repentance, and guided him ňĻrightlyňļ"
  20,123,"God said, ‚ÄúDescend, both of you, from here together ňĻwith Satanňļ as enemies to each other. Then when guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows My guidance will neither go astray ňĻin this lifeňļ nor suffer ňĻin the nextňļ"
  20,124,"But whoever turns away from My Reminder will certainly have a miserable life,¬†then We will raise them up blind on the Day of Judgment.‚ÄĚ"
  20,125,"They will cry, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Why have you raised me up blind, although I used to see?‚ÄĚ"
  20,126,"God will respond, ‚ÄúIt is so, just as Our revelations came to you and you neglected them, so Today you are neglected.‚ÄĚ"
  20,127,This is how We reward whoever transgresses and does not believe in the revelations of their Lord. And the punishment of the Hereafter is far more severe and more lasting
  20,128,"Is it not yet clear to them how many peoples We destroyed before them, whose ruins they still pass by? Surely in this are signs for people of sound judgment"
  20,129,"Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord¬†ňĻO Prophetňļ and a term already set, their ňĻinstantňļ doom would have been inevitable"
  20,130,"So be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ with what they say. And glorify the praises of your Lord before sunrise and before sunset, and glorify Him in the hours of the night and at both ends of the day,¬†so that you may be pleased ňĻwith the rewardňļ"
  20,131,"Do not let your eyes crave what We have allowed some of the disbelievers to enjoy; the ňĻfleetingňļ splendour of this worldly life, which We test them with. But your Lord‚Äôs provision ňĻin the Hereafterňļ is far better and more lasting"
  20,132,"Bid your people to pray, and be diligent in ňĻobservingňļ it. We do not ask you to provide. It is We Who provide for you. And the ultimate outcome is ňĻonlyňļ for ňĻthe people ofňļ righteousness"
  20,133,"They demand, ‚ÄúIf only he could bring us a sign from his Lord!‚ÄĚ¬†Have they not ňĻalreadyňļ received a confirmation of what is in earlier Scriptures"
  20,134,"Had We destroyed them with a torment before this ňĻProphet cameňļ, they would have surely argued, ‚ÄúOur Lord! If only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your revelations before being humiliated and put to shame.‚ÄĚ"
  20,135,"Say ňĻto them, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúEach ňĻof usňļ is waiting, so keep waiting! You will soon know who is on the Straight Path and is ňĻrightlyňļ guided.‚ÄĚ"
  21,1,"ňĻThe time ofňļ people‚Äôs judgment has drawn near, yet they are heedlessly turning away"
  21,2,"Whatever new reminder comes to them from their Lord, they only listen to it jokingly"
  21,3,"with their hearts ňĻtotallyňļ distracted. The evildoers would converse secretly, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúIs this ňĻoneňļ not human like yourselves? Would you fall for ňĻthisňļ witchcraft, even though you can ňĻclearlyňļ see?‚ÄĚ"
  21,4,"The Prophet responded, ‚ÄúMy Lord ňĻfullyňļ knows every word spoken in the heavens and the earth. For He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  21,5,"Yet they say, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is a set of confused dreams! No, he has fabricated it! No, he must be a poet! So let him bring us a ňĻtangibleňļ sign like those ňĻprophetsňļ sent before.‚ÄĚ"
  21,6,Not a ňĻsingleňļ society We destroyed before them ever believed ňĻafter receiving the signsňļ. Will these ňĻpagansňļ then believe
  21,7,"We did not send ňĻmessengersňļ before you ňĻO Prophetňļ except mere men inspired by Us. If you ňĻpolytheistsňļ do not know ňĻthis alreadyňļ, then ask those who have knowledge ňĻof the Scripturesňļ"
  21,8,"We did not give those messengers ňĻsupernaturalňļ bodies that did not need food, nor were they immortal"
  21,9,"Then We fulfilled Our promise to them, saving them along with whoever We willed and destroying the transgressors"
  21,10,"We have surely revealed to you a Book, in which there is glory for you. Will you not then understand"
  21,11,"ňĻImagineňļ how many societies of wrongdoers We have destroyed, raising up other people after them"
  21,12,"When the wrongdoers sensed ňĻthe arrival ofňļ Our torment, they started to run away from their cities"
  21,13,"ňĻThey were told,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not run away! Return to your luxuries and your homes, so you may be questioned ňĻabout your fateňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  21,14,"They cried, ‚ÄúWoe to us! We have surely been wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  21,15,"They kept repeating their cry until We mowed them down, ňĻleaving themňļ lifeless"
  21,16,We did not create the heavens and the earth and everything in between for sport
  21,17,"Had We intended to take ňĻsomeňļ amusement, We could have found it in Our presence, if that had been Our Will"
  21,18,"In fact, We hurl the truth against falsehood, leaving it crushed, and it quickly vanishes. And woe be to you for what you claim"
  21,19,"To Him belong all those in the heavens and the earth. And those nearest to Him are not too proud to worship Him, nor do they tire"
  21,20,"They glorify ňĻHimňļ day and night, never wavering"
  21,21,"Or have they taken gods from the earth, who can raise the dead"
  21,22,"Had there been other gods besides God in the heavens or the earth, both ňĻrealmsňļ would have surely been corrupted. So Glorified is God, Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  21,23,"He cannot be questioned about what He does, but they will ňĻallňļ be questioned"
  21,24,"Or have they taken other gods besides Him? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShow ňĻmeňļ your proof. Here is ňĻthe Quran,ňļ the Reminder for those with me; along with ňĻearlier Scriptures,ňļ the Reminder for those before me.‚ÄĚ¬†But most of them do not know the truth, so they turn away"
  21,25,"We never sent a messenger before you ňĻO Prophetňļ without revealing to him: ‚ÄúThere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Me, so worship Me ňĻaloneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  21,26,"And they say, ‚ÄúThe Most Compassionate has offspring!‚ÄĚ¬†Glory be to Him! In fact, those ňĻangelsňļ are only ňĻHisňļ honoured servants"
  21,27,"who do not speak until He has spoken, ňĻonlyňļ acting at His command"
  21,28,"He ňĻfullyňļ knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them. They do not intercede except for whom He approves, and they tremble in awe of Him"
  21,29,"Whoever of them were to say, ‚ÄúI am a god besides Him,‚ÄĚ they would be rewarded with Hell by Us. This is how We reward the wrongdoers"
  21,30,Do the disbelievers not realize that the heavens and earth were ňĻonceňļ one mass then We split them apart?¬†And We created from water every living thing. Will they not then believe
  21,31,"And We have placed firm mountains upon the earth so it does not shake with them, and made in it broad pathways so they may find their way"
  21,32,"And We have made the sky a well-protected canopy, still they turn away from its signs"
  21,33,"And He is the One Who created the day and the night, the sun and the moon‚ÄĒeach travelling in an orbit"
  21,34,"We have not granted immortality to any human before you ňĻO Prophetňļ: so if you die, will they live forever"
  21,35,"Every soul will taste death. And We test you ňĻO humanityňļ with good and evil as a trial, then to Us you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  21,36,"When the disbelievers see you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they only make fun of you, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúIs this the one who speaks ňĻillňļ of your gods?‚ÄĚ while they disbelieve at the mention of the Most Compassionate"
  21,37,"Humankind is made of haste. I will soon show you My signs, so do not ask Me to hasten them"
  21,38,"They ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  21,39,"If only the disbelievers knew that a time will come when they will not be able to keep the Fire off their faces or backs, nor will they be helped"
  21,40,"In fact, the Hour will take them by surprise, leaving them stunned. So they will not be able to avert it, nor will it be delayed from them"
  21,41,"ňĻOtherňļ messengers had already been ridiculed before you ňĻO Prophetňļ, but those who mocked them were overtaken by what they used to ridicule"
  21,42,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWho can defend you by day or by night against the Most Compassionate?‚ÄĚ Still they turn away from the remembrance of their Lord"
  21,43,"Or do they have gods‚ÄĒother than Us‚ÄĒthat can protect them? They cannot ňĻevenňļ protect themselves, nor will they be aided against Us"
  21,44,"In fact, We have allowed enjoyment for these ňĻMeccansňļ and their forefathers for such a long time ňĻthat they took it for grantedňļ. Do they not see that We gradually reduce ňĻtheirňļ land from its borders? Is it they who will then prevail"
  21,45,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI warn you only by revelation.‚ÄĚ But the deaf cannot hear the call when they are warned"
  21,46,"If they were touched by even a breath of your Lord‚Äôs torment, they would certainly cry, ‚ÄúWoe to us! We have really been wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  21,47,"We will set up the scales of justice on the Day of Judgment, so no soul will be wronged in the least. And ňĻevenňļ if a deed is the weight of a mustard seed, We will bring it forth. And sufficient are We as a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner"
  21,48,"Indeed, We granted Moses and Aaron the standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ‚ÄĒa light and a reminder for the righteous"
  21,49,"who are in awe of their Lord without seeing Him,¬†and are fearful of the Hour"
  21,50,And this ňĻQuranňļ is a blessed reminder which We have revealed. Will you ňĻpagansňļ then deny it
  21,51,"And indeed, We had granted Abraham sound judgment early on, for We knew him well ňĻto be worthy of itňļ"
  21,52,"ňĻRememberňļ when he questioned his father and his people, ‚ÄúWhat are these statues to which you are so devoted?‚ÄĚ"
  21,53,"They replied, ‚ÄúWe found our forefathers worshipping them.‚ÄĚ"
  21,54,"He responded, ‚ÄúIndeed, you and your forefathers have been clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  21,55,"They asked, ‚ÄúHave you come to us with the truth, or is this a joke?‚ÄĚ"
  21,56,"He replied, ‚ÄúIn fact, your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, Who created them ňĻbothňļ. And to that I bear witness.‚ÄĚ"
  21,57,"ňĻThen he said to himself,ňļ ‚ÄúBy God! I will surely plot against your idols after you have turned your backs and gone away.‚ÄĚ"
  21,58,"So he smashed them into pieces, except the biggest of them, so they might turn to it ňĻfor answersňļ"
  21,59,"They protested, ‚ÄúWho dared do this to our gods? It must be an evildoer!‚ÄĚ"
  21,60,"Some said, ‚ÄúWe heard a young man, called Abraham, speaking ňĻillňļ of them.‚ÄĚ"
  21,61,"They demanded, ‚ÄúBring him before the eyes of the people, so that they may witness ňĻhis trialňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  21,62,"They asked, ‚ÄúWas it you who did this to our gods, O Abraham?‚ÄĚ"
  21,63,"He replied ňĻsarcasticallyňļ, ‚ÄúNo, this one‚ÄĒthe biggest of them‚ÄĒdid it! So ask them, if they can talk!‚ÄĚ"
  21,64,"So they came back to their senses, saying ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúYou yourselves are truly the wrongdoers!‚ÄĚ"
  21,65,"Then they ňĻquicklyňļ regressed to their ňĻoriginalňļ mind-set, ňĻarguing,ňļ ‚ÄúYou already know that those ňĻidolsňļ cannot talk.‚ÄĚ"
  21,66,"He rebuked ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúDo you then worship‚ÄĒinstead of God‚ÄĒwhat can neither benefit nor harm you in any way"
  21,67,Shame on you and whatever you worship instead of God! Do you not have any sense?‚ÄĚ
  21,68,"They concluded, ‚ÄúBurn him up to avenge your gods, if you must act.‚ÄĚ"
  21,69,"We ordered, ‚ÄúO fire! Be cool and safe for Abraham!‚ÄĚ"
  21,70,"They had sought to harm him, but We made them the worst losers"
  21,71,"Then We delivered him, along with Lot, to the land We had showered with blessings for all people"
  21,72,"And We blessed him with Isaac ňĻas a sonňļ and Jacob ňĻas a grandsonňļ, as an additional favour‚ÄĒmaking all of them righteous"
  21,73,"We ňĻalsoňļ made them leaders, guiding by Our command, and inspired them to do good deeds, establish prayer, and pay alms-tax. And they were devoted to Our worship"
  21,74,"And to Lot We gave wisdom and knowledge, and delivered him from the society engrossed in shameful practices. They were certainly an evil, rebellious people"
  21,75,"And We admitted him into Our mercy, ňĻforňļ he was truly one of the righteous"
  21,76,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Noah had cried out to Us earlier, so We responded to him and delivered him and his family¬†from the great distress"
  21,77,"And We made him prevail over those who had rejected Our signs. They were truly an evil people, so We drowned them all"
  21,78,"And ňĻrememberňļ when David and Solomon passed judgment regarding the crops ruined ňĻat nightňļ by someone‚Äôs sheep, and We were witness to their judgments"
  21,79,"We guided ňĻyoungňļ Solomon to a fairer settlement,¬†and granted each of them wisdom and knowledge. We subjected the mountains as well as the birds to hymn ňĻOur praisesňļ along with David. It is We Who did ňĻit allňļ"
  21,80,We taught him the art of making body armour to protect you in battle. Will you then be grateful
  21,81,"And to Solomon We subjected the raging winds, blowing by his command to the land We had showered with blessings. It is We Who know everything"
  21,82,"And ňĻWe subjectedňļ some jinn¬†that dived for him,¬†and performed other duties. It is We Who kept them in check"
  21,83,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Job cried out to his Lord, ‚ÄúI have been touched with adversity,¬†and You are the Most Merciful of the merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  21,84,"So We answered his prayer and removed his adversity, and gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for the ňĻdevotedňļ worshippers"
  21,85,"And ňĻrememberňļ Ishmael, Enoch, and ‚Īęul-Kifl.¬†They were all steadfast"
  21,86,"We admitted them into Our mercy, for they were truly of the righteous"
  21,87,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the Man of the Whale stormed off ňĻfrom his cityňļ in a rage, thinking We would not restrain him.¬†Then in the ňĻveils ofňļ darkness¬†he cried out, ‚ÄúThere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except You. Glory be to You! I have certainly done wrong.‚ÄĚ"
  21,88,So We answered his prayer and rescued him from anguish. And so do We save the ňĻtrueňļ believers
  21,89,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Zachariah cried out to his Lord, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Do not leave me childless, though You are the Best of Successors.‚ÄĚ"
  21,90,"So We answered his prayer, granted him John, and made his wife fertile. Indeed, they used to race in doing good, and call upon Us with hope and fear, totally humbling themselves before Us"
  21,91,"And ňĻrememberňļ the one who guarded her chastity, so We breathed into her through Our angel, ňĻGabriel,ňļ¬†making her and her son a sign for all peoples"
  21,92,"ňĻO prophets!ňļ Indeed, this religion of yours is ňĻonlyňļ one, and I am your Lord, so worship Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  21,93,Yet the people have divided it into sects. But to Us they will all return
  21,94,"So whoever does good and is a believer will never be denied ňĻthe reward forňļ their striving, for We are recording it all"
  21,95,It is impossible for a society which We have destroyed to ever rise again
  21,96,"until ňĻafterňļ Gog and Magog have broken loose ňĻfrom the barrierňļ,¬†swarming down from every hill"
  21,97,"ushering in the True Promise.¬†Then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthe disbelievers will stare ňĻin horror, crying,ňļ ‚ÄúOh, woe to us! We have truly been heedless of this. In fact, we have been wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  21,98,Certainly you ňĻdisbelieversňļ and whatever you worship instead of God will be the fuel of Hell.¬†You are ňĻallňļ bound to enter it
  21,99,"Had those idols been ňĻtrueňļ gods, they would not have entered it. And they will be there forever"
  21,100,"In it they will groan, and will not be able to hear"
  21,101,Surely those for whom We have destined the finest reward will be kept far away from Hell
  21,102,not even hearing the slightest hissing from it. And they will delight forever in what their souls desire
  21,103,"The Supreme Horror ňĻof that Dayňļ will not disturb them, and the angels will greet them, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúThis is your Day, which you have been promised.‚ÄĚ"
  21,104,"On that Day We will roll up the heavens like a scroll of writings. Just as We produced the first creation, ňĻsoňļ shall We reproduce it. That is a promise binding on Us. We truly uphold ňĻOur promisesňļ"
  21,105,"Surely, following the ňĻheavenlyňļ Record, We decreed in the Scriptures: ‚ÄúMy righteous servants shall inherit the land.‚ÄĚ"
  21,106,Surely this ňĻQuranňļ is sufficient ňĻas a reminderňļ for those devoted to worship
  21,107,We have sent you ňĻO Prophetňļ only as a mercy for the whole world
  21,108,"Say, ‚ÄúWhat has been revealed to me is this: ‚ÄėYour God is only One God.‚Äô Will you then submit?‚ÄĚ"
  21,109,"If they turn away, then say, ‚ÄúI have warned you all equally. I do not know if what you are threatened with is near or far"
  21,110,God surely knows what you say openly and whatever you hide
  21,111,I do not know if this ňĻdelayňļ is possibly a test for you and an enjoyment for a while.‚ÄĚ
  21,112,"ňĻIn the end,ňļ the Prophet said, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Judge ňĻbetween usňļ in truth. And our Lord is the Most Compassionate, Whose help is sought against what you claim.‚ÄĚ"
  22,1,"O humanity! Fear your Lord, for the ňĻviolentňļ quaking at the Hour is surely a dreadful thing"
  22,2,"The Day you see it, every nursing mother will abandon what she is nursing, and every pregnant woman will deliver her burden ňĻprematurelyňļ. And you will see people ňĻas if they wereňļ drunk, though they will not be drunk; but the torment of God is ňĻterriblyňļ severe"
  22,3,"ňĻStillňļ there are some who dispute about God without knowledge, and follow every rebellious devil"
  22,4,It has been decreed for such devils that whoever takes them as a guide will be misguided and led by them into the torment of the Blaze
  22,5,"O humanity! If you are in doubt about the Resurrection, then ňĻknow thatňļ We did create you¬†from dust, then from a sperm-drop,¬†then ňĻdeveloped you intoňļ a clinging clot ňĻof bloodňļ,¬†then a lump of flesh‚ÄĒfully formed or unformed‚ÄĒin order to demonstrate ňĻOur powerňļ to you. ňĻThenňļ We settle whatever ňĻembryoňļ We will in the womb for an appointed term, then bring you forth as infants, so that you may reach your prime. Some of you ňĻmayňļ die ňĻyoungňļ, while others are left to reach the most feeble stage of life so that they may know nothing after having known much. And you see the earth lifeless, but as soon as We send down rain upon it, it begins to stir ňĻto lifeňļ and swell, producing every type of pleasant plant"
  22,6,"That is because God ňĻaloneňļ is the Truth, He ňĻaloneňļ gives life to the dead, and He ňĻaloneňļ is Most Capable of everything"
  22,7,"And certainly the Hour is coming, there is no doubt about it. And God will surely resurrect those in the graves"
  22,8,"ňĻStillňļ there are some who dispute about God without knowledge, guidance, or an enlightening scripture"
  22,9,"turning away ňĻin prideňļ to lead ňĻothersňļ astray from God‚Äôs Way. They will suffer disgrace in this world, and on the Day of Judgment We will make them taste the torment of burning"
  22,10,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúThis is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And God is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ"
  22,11,"And there are some who worship God on the verge ňĻof faithňļ: if they are blessed with something good, they are content with it; but if they are afflicted with a trial, they relapse ňĻinto disbeliefňļ,¬†losing this world and the Hereafter. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the clearest loss"
  22,12,They call besides God what can neither harm nor benefit them. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the farthest one can stray
  22,13,"They invoke those whose worship leads to harm, not benefit. What an evil patron and what an evil associate"
  22,14,"Indeed, God will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens, under which rivers flow. Surely God does what He wills"
  22,15,"Whoever thinks that God will not help His Prophet in this world and the Hereafter, let them stretch out a rope to the ceiling and strangle themselves, then let them see if this plan will do away with ňĻthe cause ofňļ their rage"
  22,16,And so We revealed this ňĻQuranňļ as clear verses. And God certainly guides whoever He wills
  22,17,"Indeed, the believers, Jews, Sabians,¬†Christians, Magi,¬†and the polytheists‚ÄĒGod will judge between them ňĻallňļ on Judgment Day. Surely God is a Witness over all things"
  22,18,"Do you not see that to God bow down ňĻin submissionňļ¬†all those in the heavens and all those on the earth, as well as the sun, the moon, the stars, the mountains, the trees, and ňĻallňļ living beings, as well as many humans, while many are deserving of punishment. And whoever God disgraces, none can honour. Surely God does what He wills"
  22,19,"These are two opposing groups that disagree about their Lord: as for the disbelievers, garments of Fire will be cut out for them and boiling water will be poured over their heads"
  22,20,"melting whatever is in their bellies, along with their skin"
  22,21,And awaiting them are maces of iron
  22,22,"Whenever they try to escape from Hell‚ÄĒout of anguish‚ÄĒthey will be forced back into it, ňĻand will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning!‚ÄĚ"
  22,23,"ňĻButňļ God will surely admit those who believe and do good into Gardens, under which rivers flow, where they will be adorned with bracelets of gold and pearls, and their clothing will be silk"
  22,24,"for they have been guided to the best of speech, and they have been guided to the Commendable Path"
  22,25,"Indeed, those who persist in disbelief and hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of God and from the Sacred Mosque‚ÄĒwhich We have appointed for all people, residents and visitors alike‚ÄĒalong with whoever intends to deviate by doing wrong in it,¬†We will cause them to taste a painful punishment"
  22,26,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We assigned to Abraham the site of the House, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not associate anything with Me ňĻin worshipňļ and purify My House for those who circle ňĻthe Ka‚Äôbahňļ, stand ňĻin prayerňļ, and bow and prostrate themselves"
  22,27,Call ňĻallňļ people to the pilgrimage.¬†They will come to you on foot and on every lean camel from every distant path
  22,28,"so they may obtain the benefits ňĻin storeňļ for them,¬†and pronounce the Name of God on appointed days over the sacrificial animals He has provided for them. So eat from their meat and feed the desperately poor"
  22,29,"Then let them groom themselves,¬†fulfil their vows, and circle the Ancient House.‚ÄĚ"
  22,30,"That is so. And whoever honours the rituals of God, it is best for them in the sight of their Lord. The ňĻmeat ofňļ cattle has been made lawful for you, except what has ňĻalreadyňļ been recited to you.¬†So shun the impurity of idolatry, and shun words of falsehood"
  22,31,"Be upright ňĻin devotionňļ to God, associating none with Him ňĻin worshipňļ. For whoever associates ňĻothersňļ with God is like someone who has fallen from the sky and is either snatched away by birds or swept by the wind to a remote place"
  22,32,"That is so. And whoever honours the symbols of God, it is certainly out of the piety of the heart"
  22,33,"You may benefit from sacrificial animals for an appointed term,¬†then their place of sacrifice is at the Ancient House"
  22,34,"For every community We appointed a rite of sacrifice so that they may pronounce the Name of God over the sacrificial animals He has provided for them. For your God is only One God, so submit yourselves to Him ňĻaloneňļ. And give good news ňĻO Prophetňļ to the humble"
  22,35,"those whose hearts tremble at the remembrance of God, who patiently endure whatever may befall them, and who establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for them"
  22,36,"We have made sacrificial camels ňĻand cattleňļ among the symbols of God, in which there is ňĻmuchňļ good for you. So pronounce the Name of God over them when they are lined up ňĻfor sacrificeňļ. Once they have fallen ňĻlifelessňļ on their sides, you may eat from their meat, and feed the needy‚ÄĒthose who do not beg, and those who do. In this way We have subjected these ňĻanimalsňļ to you so that you may be grateful"
  22,37,"Neither their meat nor blood reaches God. Rather, it is your piety that reaches Him. This is how He has subjected them to you so that you may proclaim the greatness of God for what He has guided you to, and give good news to the good-doers"
  22,38,"Indeed, God defends those who believe. Surely God does not like whoever is deceitful, ungrateful"
  22,39,"Permission ňĻto fight backňļ is ňĻherebyňļ granted to those being fought, for they have been wronged.¬†And God is truly Most Capable of helping them ňĻprevailňļ"
  22,40,"ňĻThey areňļ those who have been expelled from their homes for no reason other than proclaiming: ‚ÄúOur Lord is God.‚ÄĚ Had God not repelled ňĻthe aggression ofňļ some people by means of others, destruction would have surely claimed monasteries, churches, synagogues, and mosques in which God‚Äôs Name is often mentioned. God will certainly help those who stand up for Him. God is truly All-Powerful, Almighty"
  22,41,"ňĻThey areňļ those who, if established in the land by Us, would perform prayer, pay alms-tax, encourage what is good, and forbid what is evil. And with God rests the outcome of all affairs"
  22,42,"If they deny you ňĻO Prophetňļ, so did the people of Noah before them, as well as ňĻthe tribes ofňļ ‚Äô»ād and Tham√Ľd"
  22,43,"the people of Abraham, the people of Lot"
  22,44,and the residents of Midian. And Moses was denied ňĻtooňļ. But I delayed ňĻthe fate ofňļ the disbelievers ňĻuntil their appointed timeňļ then seized them. And how severe was My response
  22,45,"Many are the societies We have destroyed for persisting in wrongdoing, leaving them in total ruin. ňĻMany areňļ also the abandoned wells and lofty palaces"
  22,46,"Have they not travelled throughout the land so their hearts may reason, and their ears may listen? Indeed, it is not the eyes that are blind, but it is the hearts in the chests that grow blind"
  22,47,They challenge you ňĻO Prophetňļ to hasten the torment. And God will never fail in His promise. But a day with your Lord is indeed like a thousand years by your counting
  22,48,"Many are the societies whose end We delayed while they did wrong, then seized them. And to Me is the final return"
  22,49,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO humanity! I am only sent to you with a clear warning"
  22,50,So those who believe and do good will have forgiveness and an honourable provision
  22,51,"But those who strive to discredit Our revelations, they will be the residents of the Hellfire.‚ÄĚ"
  22,52,"Whenever We sent a messenger or a prophet before you ňĻO Prophetňļ and he recited ňĻOur revelationsňļ, Satan would influence ňĻpeople‚Äôs understanding ofňļ his recitation. But ňĻeventuallyňļ God would eliminate Satan‚Äôs influence. Then God would ňĻfirmlyňļ establish His revelations. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  22,53,All that so He may make Satan‚Äôs influence a trial for those ňĻhypocritesňļ whose hearts are sick and those ňĻdisbelieversňļ whose hearts are hardened. Surely the wrongdoers are totally engrossed in opposition
  22,54,"ňĻThis isňļ also so that those gifted with knowledge would know that this ňĻrevelationňļ is the truth from your Lord, so they have faith in it, and so their hearts would submit humbly to it. And God surely guides the believers to the Straight Path"
  22,55,"Yet the disbelievers will persist in doubt about this ňĻrevelationňļ until the Hour takes them by surprise, or the torment of a terminating¬†Day comes to them"
  22,56,All authority on that Day is for God ňĻaloneňļ.¬†He will judge between them. So those who believe and do good will be in the Gardens of Bliss
  22,57,"But those who disbelieve and deny Our revelations, it is they who will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  22,58,"As for those who emigrate in the cause of God and then are martyred or die, God will indeed grant them a good provision. Surely God is the Best Provider"
  22,59,"He will certainly admit them into a place they will be pleased with. For God is truly All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  22,60,"That is so. And whoever retaliates in equivalence to the injury they have received, and then are wronged ňĻagainňļ, God will certainly help them. Surely God is Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  22,61,"That is because God causes the night to merge into the day, and the day into the night. Indeed, God is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  22,62,"That is because God ňĻaloneňļ is the Truth and what they invoke besides Him is falsehood, and God ňĻaloneňļ is truly the Most High, All-Great"
  22,63,"Do you not see that God sends down rain from the sky, then the earth becomes green? Surely God is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  22,64,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. God ňĻaloneňļ is truly the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  22,65,Do you not see that God has subjected to you¬†whatever is in the earth as well as the ships ňĻthatňļ sail through the sea by His command? He keeps the sky from falling down on the earth except by His permission. Surely God is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to humanity
  22,66,"And He is the One Who gave you life, then will cause you to die, and then will bring you back to life. ňĻButňļ surely humankind is ever ungrateful"
  22,67,"For every community We appointed a code¬†of life to follow.¬†So do not let them dispute with you ňĻO Prophetňļ in this matter. And invite ňĻallňļ to your Lord, for you are truly on the Right Guidance"
  22,68,"But if they argue with you, then say, ‚ÄúGod knows best what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  22,69,God will judge between you ňĻallňļ on Judgment Day regarding your differences
  22,70,Do you not know that God ňĻfullyňļ knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth? Surely it is all ňĻwrittenňļ in a Record. That is certainly easy for God
  22,71,"Yet they worship besides God that for which He has sent down no authority, and of which they have no knowledge. The wrongdoers will have no helper"
  22,72,"Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, you ňĻO Prophetňļ recognize rage on the faces of the disbelievers, as if they are going to snap at those who recite Our revelations to them. Say, ‚ÄúShall I inform you of something far more enraging than that? ňĻIt isňļ the Fire with which God has threatened those who disbelieve. What an evil destination!‚ÄĚ"
  22,73,"O humanity! A lesson is set forth, so listen to it ňĻcarefullyňļ: those ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides God can never create ňĻso much asňļ a fly, even if they ňĻallňļ were to come together for that. And if a fly were to snatch anything away from them, they cannot ňĻevenňļ retrieve it from the fly. How powerless are those who invoke and those invoked"
  22,74,"They have not shown God the reverence He deserves. Surely God is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  22,75,"God selects messengers from both angels and people, for God is truly All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  22,76,He knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them. And to God ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ
  22,77,"O believers! Bow down, prostrate yourselves, worship your Lord, and do ňĻwhat isňļ good so that you may be successful"
  22,78,"Strive for ňĻthe cause ofňļ God in the way He deserves, for ňĻit isňļ He ňĻWhoňļ has chosen you, and laid upon you no hardship in the religion‚ÄĒthe way of your forefather Abraham. ňĻIt is Godňļ Who named you ‚Äėthe ones who submit‚Äô¬†ňĻin theňļ earlier ňĻScripturesňļ and in this ňĻQuranňļ, so that the Messenger may be a witness over you, and that you may be witnesses over humanity. So establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and hold fast to God. He ňĻaloneňļ is your Guardian. What an excellent Guardian, and what an excellent Helper"
  23,1,Successful indeed are the believers
  23,2,those who humble themselves in prayer
  23,3,those who avoid idle talk
  23,4,those who pay alms-tax
  23,5,those who guard their chastity
  23,6,"except with their wives or those ňĻbondwomenňļ in their possession,¬†for then they are free from blame"
  23,7,but whoever seeks beyond that are the transgressors
  23,8,ňĻthe believers are alsoňļ those who are true to their trusts and covenants
  23,9,and those who are ňĻproperlyňļ observant of their prayers
  23,10,These are the ones who will be awarded
  23,11,Paradise as their own.¬†They will be there forever
  23,12,"And indeed, We created humankind¬†from an extract of clay"
  23,13,then placed each ňĻhumanňļ as a sperm-drop¬†in a secure place
  23,14,"then We developed the drop into a clinging clot ňĻof bloodňļ, then developed the clot into a lump ňĻof fleshňļ, then developed the lump into bones, then clothed the bones with flesh, then We brought it into being as a new creation.¬†So Blessed is God, the Best of Creators"
  23,15,After that you will surely die
  23,16,then on the Day of Judgment you will be resurrected
  23,17,"And indeed, We created above you seven levels ňĻof heavenňļ. We are never unmindful of ňĻOurňļ creation"
  23,18,"We send down rain from the sky in perfect measure, causing it to soak into the earth. And We are surely able to take it away"
  23,19,"With it We produce for you gardens of palm trees and grapevines, in which there are abundant fruits, and from which you may eat"
  23,20,"as well as ňĻoliveňļ trees which grow at Mount Sinai, providing oil and a condiment to eat"
  23,21,"And there is certainly a lesson for you in cattle, from whose bellies We give you ňĻmilkňļ to drink, and in them are many other benefits for you, and from them you may eat"
  23,22,And you are carried upon ňĻsome ofňļ them and upon ships
  23,23,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people. He declared, ‚ÄúO my people! Worship God ňĻaloneňļ. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then fear ňĻHimňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  23,24,"But the disbelieving chiefs of his people said ňĻto the massesňļ, ‚ÄúThis is only a human like you, who wants to be superior to you. Had God willed, He could have easily sent down angels ňĻinsteadňļ. We have never heard of this in ňĻthe history ofňļ our forefathers"
  23,25,"He is simply insane, so bear with him for a while.‚ÄĚ"
  23,26,"Noah prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Help me, because they have denied ňĻmeňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  23,27,"So We inspired him: ‚ÄúBuild the Ark under Our ňĻwatchfulňļ Eyes and directions. Then when Our command comes and the oven bursts ňĻwith waterňļ,¬†take on board a pair from every species along with your family‚ÄĒexcept those against whom the decree ňĻto drownňļ has already been passed. And do not plead with Me for those who have done wrong, for they will surely be drowned.‚ÄĚ"
  23,28,"Then when you and those with you have settled in the Ark, say, ‚ÄúAll praise is for God, Who saved us from the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  23,29,"And pray, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Allow me a blessed landing, for You are the best accommodator.‚ÄĚ"
  23,30,Surely in this are lessons.¬†And We ňĻalwaysňļ put ňĻpeopleňļ to the test
  23,31,Then We raised another generation after them
  23,32,"and sent to them a messenger from among themselves, ňĻdeclaring,ňļ ‚ÄúWorship God ňĻaloneňļ. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then fear ňĻHimňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  23,33,"But the chiefs of his people‚ÄĒwho disbelieved, denied the meeting ňĻwith Godňļ in the Hereafter, and were spoiled by the worldly luxuries We had provided for them‚ÄĒsaid ňĻto the massesňļ, ‚ÄúThis is only a human like you. He eats what you eat, and drinks what you drink"
  23,34,"And if you ňĻeverňļ obey a human like yourselves, then you would certainly be losers"
  23,35,"Does he promise you that once you are dead and reduced to dust and bones, you will be brought forth ňĻaliveňļ"
  23,36,"Impossible, simply impossible is what you are promised"
  23,37,"There is nothing beyond our worldly life. We die, others are born, and none will be resurrected"
  23,38,"He is no more than a man who has fabricated a lie about God, and we will never believe in him.‚ÄĚ"
  23,39,"The messenger prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Help me, because they have denied ňĻmeňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  23,40,"God responded, ‚ÄúSoon they will be truly regretful.‚ÄĚ"
  23,41,"Then the ňĻmightyňļ blast overtook them with justice, and We reduced them to rubble. So away with the wrongdoing people"
  23,42,Then We raised other generations after them
  23,43,"No people can advance their doom, nor can they delay it"
  23,44,"Then We sent Our messengers in succession: whenever a messenger came to his people, they denied him. So We destroyed them, one after the other, reducing them to ňĻcautionaryňļ tales. So away with the people who refuse to believe"
  23,45,Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs¬†and compelling proof
  23,46,"to Pharaoh and his chiefs, but they behaved arrogantly and were a tyrannical people"
  23,47,"They argued, ‚ÄúWill we believe in two humans, like ourselves, whose people are slaves to us?‚ÄĚ"
  23,48,"So they rejected them both, and ňĻsoňļ were among those destroyed"
  23,49,"And We certainly gave Moses the Scripture, so perhaps his people would be ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  23,50,"And We made the son of Mary and his mother a sign, and gave them refuge on high ground‚ÄĒa ňĻsuitableňļ place for rest with flowing water"
  23,51,"O messengers! Eat from what is good and lawful, and act righteously. Indeed, I fully know what you do"
  23,52,"Surely this religion of yours is ňĻonlyňļ one, and I am your Lord, so fear Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  23,53,"Yet the people have divided it into different sects, each rejoicing in what they have"
  23,54,So leave them ňĻO Prophetňļ in their heedlessness for a while
  23,55,"Do they think, since We provide them with wealth and children"
  23,56,that We hasten to ňĻhonourňļ them ňĻwithňļ all kinds of good? No! They are not aware
  23,57,Surely those who tremble in awe of their Lord
  23,58,and who believe in the revelations of their Lord
  23,59,and who associate none with their Lord
  23,60,"and who do whatever ňĻgoodňļ they do with their hearts fearful, ňĻknowingňļ that they will return to their Lord‚ÄĒ"
  23,61,"it is they who race to do good deeds, always taking the lead"
  23,62,We never require of any soul more than what it can afford. And with Us is a record which speaks the truth. None will be wronged
  23,63,"But the hearts of those ňĻwho disbelieveňļ are oblivious to ňĻall ofňļ this,¬†and they have other ňĻevilňļ deeds, opposite to this, in which they are engrossed"
  23,64,"But as soon as We seize their elite with torment, they start to cry for help"
  23,65,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not cry for help today. Surely you will never be saved from Us"
  23,66,"Indeed, My revelations were recited to you, but you used to back away ňĻin disgustňļ"
  23,67,"boasting of the Sacred House, and babbling ňĻnonsense about the Quranňļ by night.‚ÄĚ"
  23,68,Is it because they have never contemplated the Word ňĻof Godňļ? Or ňĻbecauseňļ there has come to them something that did not come to their forefathers
  23,69,"Or ňĻbecauseňļ they failed to recognize their Messenger, and so they denied him"
  23,70,"Or ňĻbecauseňļ they say, ‚ÄúHe is insane?‚ÄĚ In fact, he has come to them with the truth, but most of them are resentful of the truth"
  23,71,"Had the truth followed their desires,¬†the heavens, the earth, and all those in them would have certainly been corrupted. In fact, We have brought them ňĻthe means toňļ their glory, but they turn away from it"
  23,72,"Or ňĻis it becauseňļ you ňĻO Prophetňļ are asking them for tribute? But the reward of your Lord is best, for He is the Best Provider"
  23,73,And surely you are calling them to the Straight Path
  23,74,but those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are certainly deviating from that Path
  23,75,"ňĻEvenňļ if We had mercy on them and removed their affliction,¬†they would still persist in their transgression, wandering blindly"
  23,76,"And We have already seized them with torment, but they never humbled themselves to their Lord, nor did they ňĻsubmissivelyňļ appeal ňĻto Himňļ"
  23,77,"But as soon as We open for them a gate of severe punishment, they will be utterly desperate"
  23,78,"He is the One Who created for you hearing, sight, and intellect. ňĻYetňļ you hardly give any thanks"
  23,79,"And He is the One Who has dispersed you ňĻallňļ over the earth, and to Him you will ňĻallňļ be gathered"
  23,80,"And He is the One Who gives life and causes death, and to Him belongs the alternation of the day and night. Will you not then understand"
  23,81,But they ňĻjustňļ say what their predecessors said
  23,82,"They said, ‚ÄúOnce we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be resurrected"
  23,83,"We have already been promised this, as well as our forefathers earlier. This is nothing but ancient fables!‚ÄĚ"
  23,84,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúTo whom belong the earth and all those on it, if you ňĻreallyňļ know?‚ÄĚ"
  23,85,"They will reply, ‚ÄúTo God!‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWhy are you not then mindful?‚ÄĚ"
  23,86,"ňĻAndňļ ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúWho is the Lord of the seven heavens and the Lord of the Mighty Throne?‚ÄĚ"
  23,87,"They will reply, ‚ÄúGod.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWill you not then fear ňĻHimňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  23,88,"Ask ňĻthem also,ňļ ‚ÄúIn Whose Hands is the authority over all things, protecting ňĻallňļ while none can protect against Him, if you ňĻreallyňļ know?‚ÄĚ"
  23,89,"They will reply, ‚ÄúGod.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúHow are you then so deluded?‚ÄĚ"
  23,90,"In fact, We have brought them the truth, and they are certainly liars"
  23,91,"God has never had ňĻanyňļ offspring, nor is there any god besides Him. Otherwise, each god would have taken away what he created, and they would have tried to dominate one another. Glorified is God above what they claim"
  23,92,ňĻHe is theňļ Knower of the seen and unseen. Exalted is He above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ
  23,93,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúMy Lord! Should You show me what they¬†are threatened with"
  23,94,"then, my Lord, do not count me among the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  23,95,We are indeed able to show you what We have threatened them with
  23,96,Respond to evil with what is best. We know well what they claim
  23,97,"And say, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I seek refuge in You from the temptations of the devils"
  23,98,"And I seek refuge in You, my Lord, that they ňĻevenňļ come near me.‚ÄĚ"
  23,99,"When death approaches any of them, they cry, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Let me go back"
  23,100,so I may do good in what I left behind.‚ÄĚ Never! It is only a ňĻuselessňļ appeal they make. And there is a barrier behind them until the Day they are resurrected
  23,101,"Then, when the Trumpet will be blown,¬†there will be no kinship between them on that Day, nor will they ňĻeven care toňļ ask about one another"
  23,102,"As for those whose scale is heavy ňĻwith good deedsňļ, it is they who will be successful"
  23,103,"But those whose scale is light, they will have doomed themselves, staying in Hell forever"
  23,104,"The Fire will burn their faces, leaving them deformed"
  23,105,"ňĻIt will be said,ňļ ‚ÄúWere My revelations not recited to you, but you used to deny them?‚ÄĚ"
  23,106,"They will cry, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Our ill-fate took hold of us, so we became a misguided people"
  23,107,"Our Lord! Take us out of this ňĻFireňļ. Then if we ever return ňĻto denialňļ, we will truly be wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  23,108,"God will respond, ‚ÄúBe despised in there! Do not ňĻeverňļ plead with Me ňĻagainňļ"
  23,109,"Indeed, there was a group of My servants who used to pray, ‚ÄėOur Lord! We have believed, so forgive us and have mercy on us, for You are the best of those who show mercy,‚Äô"
  23,110,but you were ňĻso busyňļ making fun of them that it made you forget My remembrance. And you used to laugh at them
  23,111,"Today I have indeed rewarded them for their perseverance: they are certainly the triumphant.‚ÄĚ"
  23,112,"He will ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúHow many years did you remain on earth?‚ÄĚ"
  23,113,"They will reply, ‚ÄúWe remained ňĻonlyňļ a day or part of a day.¬†But ask those who kept count.‚ÄĚ"
  23,114,"He will say, ‚ÄúYou only remained for a little while, if only you knew"
  23,115,"Did you then think that We had created you without purpose, and that you would never be returned to Us?‚ÄĚ"
  23,116,"Exalted is God, the True King! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him, the Lord of the Honourable Throne"
  23,117,"Whoever invokes, besides God, another god‚ÄĒfor which they can have no proof‚ÄĒthey will surely find their penalty with their Lord. Indeed, the disbelievers will never succeed"
  23,118,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúMy Lord! Forgive and have mercy, for You are the best of those who show mercy.‚ÄĚ"
  24,1,"ňĻThis isňļ a s√Ľrah¬†which We have revealed and made ňĻits rulingsňļ obligatory, and revealed in it clear commandments so that you may be mindful"
  24,2,"As for female and male fornicators, give each of them one hundred lashes,¬†and do not let pity for them make you lenient in ňĻenforcingňļ the law of God, if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe in God and the Last Day. And let a number of believers witness their punishment"
  24,3,A male fornicator would only marry a female fornicator or idolatress. And a female fornicator would only be married to a fornicator or idolater. This is ňĻallňļ forbidden to the believers
  24,4,"Those who accuse chaste women ňĻof adulteryňļ and fail to produce four witnesses, give them eighty lashes ňĻeachňļ. And do not ever accept any testimony from them‚ÄĒfor they are indeed the rebellious‚ÄĒ"
  24,5,"except those who repent afterwards and mend their ways, then surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  24,6,"And those who accuse their wives ňĻof adulteryňļ but have no witness except themselves, the accuser must testify,¬†swearing four times by God that he is telling the truth"
  24,7,and a fifth oath that God may condemn him if he is lying
  24,8,"For her to be spared the punishment, she must swear four times by God that he is telling a lie"
  24,9,and a fifth oath that God may be displeased with her if he is telling the truth
  24,10,"ňĻYou would have suffered,ňļ had it not been for God‚Äôs grace and mercy upon you, and had God not been Accepting of Repentance, All-Wise"
  24,11,"Indeed, those who came up with that ňĻoutrageousňļ slander are a group of you. Do not think this is bad for you. Rather, it is good for you.¬†They will be punished, each according to their share of the sin. As for their mastermind,¬†he will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  24,12,"If only the believing men and women had thought well of one another, when you heard this ňĻrumourňļ, and said, ‚ÄúThis is clearly ňĻan outrageousňļ slander!‚ÄĚ"
  24,13,"Why did they not produce four witnesses? Now, since they have failed to produce witnesses, they are ňĻtrulyňļ liars in the sight of God"
  24,14,"Had it not been for God‚Äôs grace and mercy upon you in this world and the Hereafter, you would have certainly been touched with a tremendous punishment for what you plunged into‚ÄĒ"
  24,15,"when you passed it from one tongue to the other, and said with your mouths what you had no knowledge of, taking it lightly while it is ňĻextremelyňļ serious in the sight of God"
  24,16,"If only you had said upon hearing it, ‚ÄúHow can we speak about such a thing! Glory be to You ňĻO Lordňļ! This is a heinous slander!‚ÄĚ"
  24,17,"God forbids you from ever doing something like this again, if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  24,18,"And God makes ňĻHisňļ commandments clear to you, for God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  24,19,"Indeed, those who love to see indecency spread among the believers will suffer a painful punishment in this life and the Hereafter. God knows and you do not know"
  24,20,"ňĻYou would have suffered,ňļ had it not been for God‚Äôs grace and mercy upon you, and had God not been Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  24,21,"O believers! Do not follow the footsteps of Satan. Whoever follows Satan‚Äôs footsteps, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ he surely bids ňĻall toňļ immorality and wickedness. Had it not been for God‚Äôs grace and mercy upon you, none of you would have ever been purified. But God purifies whoever He wills. And God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  24,22,"Do not let the people of virtue and affluence among you swear to suspend donations to their relatives, the needy, and the emigrants in the cause of God. Let them pardon and forgive. Do you not love to be forgiven by God? And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  24,23,"Surely those who accuse chaste, unsuspecting,¬†believing women are cursed in this life and the Hereafter. And they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  24,24,"on the Day their tongues, hands, and feet will testify against them for what they used to do"
  24,25,"On that Day, God will give them their just penalty in full, and they will ňĻcome toňļ know that God ňĻaloneňļ is the Ultimate Truth"
  24,26,"Wicked women are for wicked men, and wicked men are for wicked women. And virtuous women are for virtuous men, and virtuous men are for virtuous women. The virtuous are innocent of what the wicked say. They will have forgiveness and an honourable provision"
  24,27,"O believers! Do not enter any house other than your own until you have asked for permission and greeted its occupants. This is best for you, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  24,28,"If you find no one at home, do not enter it until you have been given permission. And if you are asked to leave, then leave. That is purer for you. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of what you do"
  24,29,There is no blame on you if you enter public places¬†where there is something of benefit for you. And God knows what you reveal and what you conceal
  24,30,ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Tell the believing men to lower their gaze and guard their chastity. That is purer for them. Surely God is All-Aware of what they do
  24,31,"And tell the believing women to lower their gaze and guard their chastity, and not to reveal their adornments¬†except what normally appears.¬†Let them draw their veils over their chests, and not reveal their ňĻhiddenňļ adornments¬†except to their husbands, their fathers, their fathers-in-law, their sons, their stepsons, their brothers, their brothers‚Äô sons or sisters‚Äô sons, their fellow women, those ňĻbondwomenňļ in their possession, male attendants with no desire, or children who are still unaware of women‚Äôs nakedness. Let them not stomp their feet, drawing attention to their hidden adornments. Turn to God in repentance all together, O believers, so that you may be successful"
  24,32,"Marry off the ňĻfreeňļ singles among you, as well as the righteous of your bondmen and bondwomen. If they are poor, God will enrich them out of His bounty. For God is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  24,33,"And let those who do not have the means to marry keep themselves chaste until God enriches them out of His bounty. And if any of those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in your possession desires a deed of emancipation, make it possible for them, if you find goodness in them. And give them some of God‚Äôs wealth which He has granted you. Do not force your ňĻslaveňļ girls into prostitution for your own worldly gains while they wish to remain chaste. And if someone coerces them, then after such a coercion God is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful ňĻto themňļ"
  24,34,"Indeed, We have sent down to you clear revelations, along with examples of those who had gone before you, and a lesson to the God-fearing"
  24,35,"God is the Light of the heavens and the earth. His light¬†is like a niche in which there is a lamp, the lamp is in a crystal, the crystal is like a shining star, lit from ňĻthe oil ofňļ a blessed olive tree, ňĻlocatedňļ neither to the east nor the west,¬†whose oil would almost glow, even without being touched by fire. Light upon light! God guides whoever He wills to His light. And God sets forth parables for humanity. For God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  24,36,"ňĻThat light shinesňļ through houses ňĻof worshipňļ which God has ordered to be raised, and where His Name is mentioned. He is glorified there morning and evening"
  24,37,"by men¬†who are not distracted‚ÄĒeither by buying or selling‚ÄĒfrom God‚Äôs remembrance, or performing prayer, or paying alms-tax. They fear a Day when hearts and eyes will tremble"
  24,38,"ňĻhopingňļ that God may reward them according to the best of their deeds, and increase them out of His grace. And God provides for whoever He wills without limit"
  24,39,"As for the disbelievers, their deeds are like a mirage in a desert, which the thirsty perceive as water, but when they approach it, they find it to be nothing. Instead, they find God there ňĻin the Hereafter, readyňļ to settle their account. And God is swift in reckoning"
  24,40,"Or ňĻtheir deeds areňļ like the darkness in a deep sea, covered by waves upon waves,¬†topped by ňĻdarkňļ clouds. Darkness upon darkness! If one stretches out their hand, they can hardly see it. And whoever God does not bless with light will have no light"
  24,41,"Do you not see that God is glorified by all those in the heavens and the earth, even the birds as they soar? Each ňĻinstinctivelyňļ knows their manner of prayer and glorification. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all they do"
  24,42,To God ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And to God is the final return
  24,43,"Do you not see that God gently drives the clouds, then joins them together, piling them up into masses, from which you see raindrops come forth? And He sends down from the sky mountains ňĻof cloudsňļ loaded with hail, pouring it on whoever He wills and averting it from whoever He wills. The flash of the clouds‚Äô lightning nearly takes away eyesight"
  24,44,God alternates the day and night. Surely in this is a lesson for people of insight
  24,45,"And God has created from water every living creature. Some of them crawl on their bellies, some walk on two legs, and some walk on four. God creates whatever He wills. Surely God is Most Capable of everything"
  24,46,We have indeed sent down revelations clarifying ňĻthe truthňļ. But God ňĻonlyňļ guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path
  24,47,"And the hypocrites say, ‚ÄúWe believe in God and the Messenger, and we obey.‚ÄĚ Then a group of them turns away soon after that. These are not ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  24,48,"And as soon as they are called to God and His Messenger so he may judge between them, a group of them¬†turns away"
  24,49,"But if the truth is in their favour, they come to him, fully submitting"
  24,50,"Is there a sickness in their hearts? Or are they in doubt? Or do they fear that God and His Messenger will be unjust to them? In fact, it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  24,51,"The only response of the ňĻtrueňļ believers, when they are called to God and His Messenger so he may judge between them, is to say, ‚ÄúWe hear and obey.‚ÄĚ It is they who will ňĻtrulyňļ succeed"
  24,52,"For whoever obeys God and His Messenger, and fears God and is mindful of Him, then it is they who will ňĻtrulyňļ triumph"
  24,53,"They swear by God their most solemn oaths that if you ňĻO Prophetňļ were to command them, they would certainly march forth ňĻin God‚Äôs causeňļ. Say, ‚ÄúňĻYouňļ do not ňĻhave toňļ swear; your obedience is well known!‚ÄĚ¬†Surely God is All-Aware of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  24,54,"Say, ‚ÄúObey God and obey the Messenger. But if you turn away, then he is only responsible for his duty¬†and you are responsible for yours.¬†And if you obey him, you will be ňĻrightlyňļ guided. The Messenger‚Äôs duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly.‚ÄĚ"
  24,55,"God has promised those of you who believe and do good that He will certainly make them successors in the land, as He did with those before them; and will surely establish for them their faith which He has chosen for them; and will indeed change their fear into security‚ÄĒňĻprovided thatňļ they worship Me, associating nothing with Me. But whoever disbelieves after this ňĻpromiseňļ, it is they who will be the rebellious"
  24,56,"Moreover, establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"
  24,57,"Do not think ňĻO Prophetňļ that the disbelievers can escape in the land. The Fire will be their home. Indeed, what an evil destination"
  24,58,"O believers! Let those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in your possession and those of you who are still under age ask for your permission ňĻto come inňļ at three times: before dawn prayer, when you take off your ňĻouterňļ clothes at noon, and after the late evening prayer. ňĻThese areňļ three times of privacy for you. Other than these times, there is no blame on you or them to move freely, attending to one another. This is how God makes the revelations clear to you, for God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  24,59,"And when your children reach the age of puberty, let them seek permission ňĻto come inňļ, as their seniors do. This is how God makes His revelations clear to you, for God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  24,60,"As for elderly women past the age of marriage, there is no blame on them if they take off their ňĻouterňļ garments, without revealing their adornments. But it is better for them if they avoid this ňĻaltogetherňļ. And God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  24,61,"There is no restriction on the blind, or the disabled, or the sick.¬†Nor on yourselves if you eat from your homes,¬†or the homes of your fathers, or your mothers, or your brothers, or your sisters, or your paternal uncles, or your paternal aunts, or your maternal uncles, or your maternal aunts, or from the homes in your trust, or ňĻthe homes ofňļ your friends. There is no blame on you eating together or separately. However, when you enter houses, greet one another with a greeting ňĻof peaceňļ from God, blessed and good.¬†This is how God makes His revelations clear to you, so perhaps you will understand"
  24,62,"The ňĻtrueňļ believers are only those who believe in God and His Messenger, and when they are with him on a public matter, they do not leave without his permission. Indeed, those who ask your permission ňĻO Prophetňļ are the ones who ňĻtrulyňļ believe in God and His Messenger. So when they ask your permission for a private matter, grant permission to whoever you wish and ask God‚Äôs forgiveness for them. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  24,63,"Do not treat the Messenger‚Äôs summons to you ňĻas lightlyňļ as your summons to one another.¬†God certainly knows those of you who slip away, hiding behind others.¬†So let those who disobey his orders beware, for an affliction may befall them, or a painful torment may overtake them"
  24,64,"Surely to God belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. He knows well what you stand for. And ňĻonňļ the Day all will be returned to Him, He will inform them of what they did. For God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  25,1,"Blessed is the One Who sent down the Standard¬†to His servant,¬†so that he may be a warner to the whole world"
  25,2,"ňĻGod isňļ the One to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, Who has never had ňĻanyňļ offspring, nor does He have a partner in ňĻgoverningňļ the kingdom. He has created everything, ordaining it precisely"
  25,3,"Yet they have taken besides Him gods who cannot create anything but are themselves created. Nor can they protect or benefit themselves. Nor can they control life, death, or resurrection"
  25,4,"The disbelievers say, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is nothing but a fabrication which he¬†made up with the help of others.‚ÄĚ Their claim is totally unjustified and untrue"
  25,5,"And they say, ‚ÄúňĻThese revelations are onlyňļ ancient fables which he has had written down, and they are rehearsed to him morning and evening.‚ÄĚ"
  25,6,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ has been revealed by the One Who knows the secrets of the heavens and the earth. Surely He is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  25,7,"And they say ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhat kind of messenger is this who eats food and goes about in market-places ňĻfor a livingňļ? If only an angel had been sent down with him to be his co-warner"
  25,8,"or a treasure had been cast down to him, or he had had a garden from which he may eat!‚ÄĚ And the wrongdoers say ňĻto the believersňļ, ‚ÄúYou are only following a bewitched man.‚ÄĚ"
  25,9,See ňĻO Prophetňļ how they call you names!¬†So they have gone so ňĻfarňļ astray that they cannot find the ňĻRightňļ Way
  25,10,"Blessed is the One Who‚ÄĒif He wills‚ÄĒcan give you far better than ňĻallňļ that: gardens under which rivers flow, and palaces as well"
  25,11,"In fact, they deny the Hour.¬†And for the deniers of the Hour, We have prepared a blazing Fire"
  25,12,"Once it sees them from a distance, they will hear it fuming and growling"
  25,13,"And when they are tossed into a narrow place inside ňĻHellňļ, chained together, then and there they will cry out for ňĻinstantňļ destruction"
  25,14,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not cry only once for destruction, but cry many times over!‚ÄĚ"
  25,15,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIs this better or the Garden of Eternity which the righteous have been promised, as a reward and ňĻan ultimateňļ destination"
  25,16,"There they will have whatever they wish for, forever. That is a promise ňĻto be sought afterňļ, binding on your Lord.‚ÄĚ"
  25,17,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day He will gather them along with what they used to worship besides God, and ask ňĻthe objects of worshipňļ,¬†‚ÄúWas it you who misled these servants of Mine, or did they stray from the Way ňĻon their ownňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  25,18,"They will say, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! It was not right for ňĻothers likeňļ us to take any lords besides You,¬†but You allowed enjoyment for them and their forefathers ňĻfor so longňļ that they forgot ňĻYourňļ remembrance and became a doomed people.‚ÄĚ"
  25,19,"ňĻThe doomed will be toldňļ, ‚ÄúYour gods have clearly denied your claims. So now you can neither ward off ňĻthe punishmentňļ nor get any help.‚ÄĚ And whoever of you does wrong, We will make them taste a horrible punishment"
  25,20,"We never sent any messenger before you ňĻO Prophetňļ, who did not eat food and go about in market-places. We have made some of you a trial for others. Will you ňĻnot thenňļ be patient? And your Lord is All-Seeing"
  25,21,"Those who do not expect to meet Us say, ‚ÄúIf only the angels were sent down to us, or we could see our Lord!‚ÄĚ They have certainly been carried away by their arrogance and have entirely exceeded all limits"
  25,22,"ňĻButňļ on the Day they will see the angels, there will be no good news for the wicked, who will cry, ‚ÄúKeep away! Away ňĻfrom usňļ!‚ÄĚ"
